As a Frontend | React Developer I have to use so many resources for various needs. I'm sharing some of my favorite resources below

1. We see many designs like Wave on different websites which also look very beautiful. If you want to give some of these designs to your website then go to this website

- https://getwaves.io/

2. Many times we need different shapes and sizes for our website design, For this, you can go to this website

- https://www.blobmaker.app/

3. Now if you want to get more of these together, you can go to the website below. There are things like Blurry background, Blurry gradient, poly grid, circle scatter, blob scene, layered waves, stacked waves, polygon scatter, symbol scatter and many more...

- https://app.haikei.app/

4. Web-based mockup tool that you can easily use from here ..

- https://smartmockups.com

5. Here is another small but nice thing you can check

- https://smalldev.tools

6. DailyDev. This is very important to me. I think everyone should have this extension. This extension is like a newspaper for developers. From here you will find huge information on various topics. And there is another platform called dev.to. This is also a great platform.

- Search for daily dev extension for chrome and install it in your browser

7. PFP. If you want to use user/profile type image for your website then you can use this one, also you can edit in this website easily.

- https://pfpmaker.com

8. Neumorphism CSS Generator

- https://lnkd.in/grvA7j3T

9. Sometimes If I need to use box-shadow, or want to use box-shadow quickly then I go to this website. It is helpful if you need to set some box-shadow effect without wasting time.

- https://lnkd.in/g5hYPMQ6

10. Javascript event keycode

- https://keycode.info/

11. Beautiful hand-crafted SVG icons,
by the makers of Tailwind CSS. No CDN or package required. Just copy svg or jsx format.

https://heroicons.com/

12. 6000+ icons — iconsax v1.0 by ©Vuesax. This one deserves heart. Just duplicate it on Figma and use it.

https://lnkd.in/gWXFwDrc

13.  cssreference.io is a free visual guide to CSS. It features the most popular properties, and explains them with illustrated and animated examples.

- https://cssreference.io/

14. Learn how to design beautiful user interfaces by yourself using specific tactics explained from a developer's point-of-view.

- https://lnkd.in/gFePSzFf?

15. Checklist Design - A collection of the best design practices.

-https://lnkd.in/g77SEGfp

16. 30 Day Vanilla JS Coding Challenge

- https://javascript30.com/

That's it for today. Thank you. I hope this will help you. Also if you have any kind of resource then you can share it in the comment section. Sharing is caring.

